<br>
You still have the carry over damage from the last hit from the monk. And how hard does that monk hit? My guess his max is probably at least 100+. hell, thats probably his average.. <br>
<br>
Furthermore, the above poster is right, the problem with percentages/heals is that extra percentage that is sometimes considered with casting a heal spell. The percentages themselves aren't terribly inaccurate.<br>
<br>
In truth, both tactics work well, and still both supply a ballpark figure at which we can view.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/usiryakk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sir Yakk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#333333>(8/29/02 9:27:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=640.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Both have errors</span><hr size=1> Both have errors.<br>
<br>
Quantify them.<br>
<br>
Have the monk record last hit, and time of the hit before it.<br>
<br>
Pet HP &lt; Pet_Regen * Most_Ticks_Until_Last_Hit + Total_Monk_Damage<br>
<br>
Pet HP &gt; Pet_Regen * Least_Ticks_Until_2ndLast_Hit + Total_Monk_Damage - Last_Monk_Hit<br>
<br>
For the % based tests, realize the %s are rounded.<br>
<br>
How are they rounded?  I don't know.<br>
<br>
Thus:<br>
The Garrison's nuke:<br>
2205 / .52 &gt; Epic_Pet_HP &gt; 2205 / .54<br>
4241 &gt; Epic_Pet_HP &gt; 4083<br>
<br>
This seems to indicate that the epic pets HPs are higher than the monk-damage parsing would imply.<br>
<br>
You might want to repeat this experiment, and make sure you saw 53%.<br>
<br>
The Heal:<br>
580 / .13 &gt; Epic_Pet_HP &gt; 580 / .15<br>
4462 &gt; Epic_Pet_HP &gt; 3866<br>
<br>
The heal has a large margin of error.  =)<br>
<br>
I would, however, be seriously tempted to use large nukes to determine pet hps.  Make preliminary guesses, then nuke all at once for just more and just less than what you figure the pet has for HPs.<br>
<br>
Criticals will be annoying, but every pet kill/not kill gives you yet another datapoint.<br>
<br>
Arenas are best for this.<br>
